  16. (** Last-in first-out stacks.

  18.    This module implements stacks (LIFOs), with in-place modification.
  19. *)

  21. (** {b Unsynchronized accesses} *)

  23. [@@@alert unsynchronized_access
  24.     "Unsynchronized accesses to stacks are a programming error."
  25. ]

  27. (**
  28.     Unsynchronized accesses to a stack may lead to an invalid queue state.
  29.     Thus, concurrent accesses to stacks must be synchronized (for instance
  30.     with a {!Mutex.t}).
  31. *)

  33. ‌type !'a t
  34. (** The type of stacks containing elements of type ['a]. *)

  36. exception Empty
  37. (** Raised when {!Stack.pop} or {!Stack.top} is applied to an empty stack. *)


  40. ‌val create : unit -> 'a t
  41. (** Return a new stack, initially empty. *)

  43. ‌val push : 'a -> 'a t -> unit
  44. (** [push x s] adds the element [x] at the top of stack [s]. *)

  46. ‌val pop : 'a t -> 'a
  47. (** [pop s] removes and returns the topmost element in stack [s],
  48.    or raises {!Empty} if the stack is empty. *)

  50. ‌val pop_opt : 'a t -> 'a option
  51. (** [pop_opt s] removes and returns the topmost element in stack [s],
  52.    or returns [None] if the stack is empty.
  53.    @since 4.08 *)

  55. ‌val drop : 'a t -> unit
  56. (** [drop s] removes the topmost element in stack [s],
  57.    or raises {!Empty} if the stack is empty.
  58.    @since 5.1 *)

  60. ‌val top : 'a t -> 'a
  61. (** [top s] returns the topmost element in stack [s],
  62.    or raises {!Empty} if the stack is empty. *)

  64. ‌val top_opt : 'a t -> 'a option
  65. (** [top_opt s] returns the topmost element in stack [s],
  66.    or [None] if the stack is empty.
  67.    @since 4.08 *)

  69. ‌val clear : 'a t -> unit
  70. (** Discard all elements from a stack. *)

  72. ‌val copy : 'a t -> 'a t
  73. (** Return a copy of the given stack. *)

  75. ‌val is_empty : 'a t -> bool
  76. (** Return [true] if the given stack is empty, [false] otherwise. *)

  78. ‌val length : 'a t -> int
  79. (** Return the number of elements in a stack. Time complexity O(1) *)

  81. ‌val iter : ('a -> unit) -> 'a t -> unit
  82. (** [iter f s] applies [f] in turn to all elements of [s],
  83.    from the element at the top of the stack to the element at the
  84.    bottom of the stack. The stack itself is unchanged. *)

  86. ‌val fold : ('acc -> 'a -> 'acc) -> 'acc -> 'a t -> 'acc
  87. (** [fold f accu s] is [(f (... (f (f accu x1) x2) ...) xn)]
  88.     where [x1] is the top of the stack, [x2] the second element,
  89.     and [xn] the bottom element. The stack is unchanged.
  90.     @since 4.03 *)

  92. (** {1 Stacks and Sequences} *)

  94. ‌val to_seq : 'a t -> 'a Seq.t
  95. (** Iterate on the stack, top to bottom.
  96.     It is safe to modify the stack during iteration.
  97.     @since 4.07 *)

  99. ‌val add_seq : 'a t -> 'a Seq.t -> unit
  100. (** Add the elements from the sequence on the top of the stack.
  101.     @since 4.07 *)

  103. ‌val of_seq : 'a Seq.t -> 'a t
  104. (** Create a stack from the sequence.
  105.     @since 4.07 *)
